The Italian cabinet Friday chose 37 undersecretaries  of state, 12 of them neo-fascists.
The previous governmment had 39 undersecretaries of state.
The list means that the neo-fascist National Alliance has either a  minister or an undersecretary in each ministry.
Thirteen of the new posts went to members of Prime Minister Silvio  Berlusconi's Forza Italia, 10 to the federalist Northern League and two to the  Democratic-Christian Centre.
